# backup-repos.conf — per-machine repo backup list for daily-backup.sh
#
# Copy this file to ~/.claude/backup-repos.conf and edit it for THIS machine.
# It is read at 02:00 by the com.clarkhager.daily-backup launchd job. This list
# is intentionally per-machine and is NOT tracked in git — different machines
# back up different repo sets.
#
# Format (one repo per line):   name | path | pull_first
#   path        absolute, or ~-relative (e.g. ~/Documents/Claude/Projects/MyRepo)
#   pull_first  true  -> repo is written by a remote/server writer (e.g. a sync
#                        service or server-side committer). Pull its commits
#                        ff-only before committing local edits; skip the repo on
#                        real divergence so a second writer never makes the
#                        conflict worse.
#               false -> normal repo, just commit + push local changes (default).
#
# Lines starting with # are ignored. Delete the placeholders below and add your
# own. Nothing is backed up until you list at least one repo.
#
# MyVault   | ~/Documents/Claude/Projects/MyVault   | true
# MyNotes   | ~/Documents/Claude/Projects/MyNotes   | false
